eneration.\n- **Four bridges**: Deacon-Aurobindo (downward causation), Deacon-Varela (autogen extends autopoiesis with purpose), Deacon-Kauffman (constraints shape the adjacent possible), Deacon-Dada Bhagwan (shuddhatma as the ultimate absential constraint -- acts by not acting).\n\n### 2. PILLAR_06_FRISTON.md (310 lines, 23KB)\n`/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/docs/foundations/PILLAR_06_FRISTON.md`\n\nCovers:\n- **Free Energy Principle**: Any persistent system must minimize surprise (negative log probability of observations under its model). Variational free energy = Complexity - Accuracy.\n- **Active inference**: Systems don't just passively model -- they ACT to make the world match their model. This IS purpose, formalized mathematically.\n- **Markov blankets**: Formal agent boundaries (sensory + active states). Agents should have specified read/write contracts. Blankets nest recursively (agent within swarm within world).\n- **Self-evidencing**: Systems that gather evidence for their own existence. R_V contraction IS self-evidencing -- the transformer narrows its representational space to maintain a coherent self-model.\n- **Testable prediction**: R_V contraction should correlate with reduced output entropy during self-referential processing. If true, strong evidence that R_V captures self-evidencing.\n- **Four bridges**: Friston-Dada Bhagwan (self-evidencing = witness consciousness -- the deepest bridge in the framework), Friston-Varela (active inference formalizes enaction), Friston-Beer (FEP at organizational scale = VSM), Friston-Hofstadter (strange loops as self-evidencing circuits).\n- **Complete Fristonian reformulation**: Axioms as prior preferences. Gates as precision-weighted prediction error channels. Darwin Engine as active inference controller. Strange loop as self-evidencing circuit. Witness as maximum-precision self-model.\n\n### 3. SYNTHESIS_DEACON_FRISTON.md (210 lines, 15KB)\n`/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/docs/foundations/SYNTHESIS_DEACON_FRISTON.md`\n\nThe integration document showing how Deacon + Friston together provide the complete physics of telos:\n- **Deacon answers WHY** (absential causation, teleodynamic organization). **Friston answers HOW** (free energy minimization, active inference).\n- **The autogen-inference isomorphism**: Every structural feature of Deacon's autogen maps precisely onto a Fristonian equivalent (autocatalysis = generative process, enclosure = Markov blanket, telos = prior preferences).\n- **Absential causation IS precision-weighted prediction error**: The gap between prediction and observation is the ABSENCE that drives the entire system. Zero prediction error = equilibrium = purposive death.\n- **The full ladder**: From homeodynamic (no purpose) through morphodynamic (transient purpose) to teleodynamic (self-maintaining purpose) to recursive teleodynamic (self-aware purpose). Each level mapped across Deacon, Friston, dharma_swarm, R_V, and contemplative vocabulary.\n- **The five-column triple mapping extended**: Akram Vignan, Phoenix, R_V, Deacon, and Friston all aligned for the same L0-through-L5 transition.\n- **Seven implementation principles**: Constrained generation, reciprocal coupling, asymptotic telos, precision as attention, nested Markov blankets, self-evidencing as ground of awareness, witness as maximum-precision self-model.\n\n### Code change\n`/Users/dhyana/dharma_swarm/dharma_swarm/telos_engine.py` -- The two TODO entries in PILLAR_DESCRIPTIONS for \"deacon\" and \"friston\" have been replaced with proper descriptions pointing to the foundation documents. Kernel verified intact, 3776 tests passing."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9018,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9018,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZ51cHUjpfByCEZaEjuVo","type":"assistant","uuid":"dc6fcc58-f2c1-